{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure boundary is model classification quality on real explicit imagery. A mocked classifier can trivially return 'flagged' and miss real false negatives/threshold behavior from the vision model.","test_description":"Submit a curated explicit-image test set through the real moderation endpoint with the real vision model enabled, then assert posts are held (not published) and moderation state is 'requires_human_review'. Include repeated runs to detect model/output variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a robustness/quality claim about the real text model's semantic detection under obfuscation. In-process mocks would hide real tokenization/normalization/model weaknesses.","test_description":"Send a corpus of hate-speech examples with leetspeak and unicode lookalikes to the real text moderation path, and assert each is flagged and held for review. Track miss rate across multiple runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The key risk is orchestration/state-transition bugs between classifier outputs, hold/publish routing, and persistence. A single unit test is too narrow; real model quality is not the primary boundary here.","test_description":"Run the moderation service with local DB/queue and stub classifiers returning 'safe' for both image/text, submit posts, then assert published status is persisted and no hold record exists. Also assert no message is lost between intake and publish store.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end SLO across multiple agentic steps in sequence. Mocked model calls would hide real latency and variance, and isolated tests miss cross-step tail-latency accumulation.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions through the production-like pipeline with real image and text model calls enabled; measure p95/p99 completion from submit timestamp to final decision, and assert under 5s at peak-like concurrent load.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.7}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on real failure modes from external model unavailability (timeouts, 5xx, connection resets). Simple mocks can miss retry classification and transport-level behavior.","test_description":"In a staging environment, induce real vision dependency outages (e.g., block outbound route or return real 5xx/timeouts from a test endpoint), submit image posts, and assert they enter retry queue with backoff metadata and are not auto-approved/published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The risk is real-model output instability on borderline content; deterministic mocks would always appear consistent and miss the true variance profile.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly within the defined short window using the real vision model path, then assert decision consistency meets policy (e.g., identical outcome or bounded flip rate) and verify any consistency layer (cache/sticky decision) is applied.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0.25}}]}
